721778f-b.title: Manhattan: Madison Avenue - 121st Street
721778f-b.text:
(1)
Mt. Morris Park, eastern side, view east, showing the Russian
Orthodox Church of Christ the Saviour (originally the Pilgrim
Congregational Church), at Madison Avenue and 121st Street,
in the background.
July 24, 1932.
P. 1  .. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, closer to the church.
July 24, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

721779f-a.title: Manhattan: Madison Avenue - 121st Street
721779f-a.text:
Mt. Morris Park, south side (120th Street) view northeast, showing
the old Pilgrim Church in the background. This church was origi
built for the Congregationists of Harlem, but has lost its origir
congregation, and is, at the time of this picture, the Russian
Qrthodox Church of Christ the Saviour.
July 25, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
